1
00:00:05,317 --> 00:00:10,695
This body is the biological expression
of the soul’s delusion;

2
00:00:10,695 --> 00:00:13,686
it’s constructed
of exploiting tendencies.

3
00:00:13,686 --> 00:00:17,938
[Facebook | Egocentric World]

4
00:00:17,938 --> 00:00:29,948
So, as we abandon envisioning ourselves
as exploiting agents,

5
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:35,436
and become dedicating agents,
we start reconceiving that

6
00:00:35,436 --> 00:00:45,716
I can achieve my potential, 
my prospect, my identity

7
00:00:45,716 --> 00:00:52,266
through service, through dedication,
not through exploitation.

8
00:00:52,271 --> 00:00:55,232
tad viddhi praṇipātena
paripraśnena sevayā 
[Bg: 4.34]

9
00:00:55,232 --> 00:00:59,095
Saraswatī 􏰅Ṭhākur said this,
“When we are bowing

10
00:00:59,095 --> 00:01:01,935
and approaching the lotus feet of guru,
and we are bowing,”

11
00:01:01,935 --> 00:01:06,925
once he said, “It means 
we are finished with this world.”

12
00:01:06,925 --> 00:01:10,050
What does that mean?
The world, where we thought,

13
00:01:10,050 --> 00:01:13,896
“I am the centre”,—
the egocentric world—

14
00:01:13,896 --> 00:01:20,789
“I am the centre, and I have
so many friends on Facebook.”

15
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:22,529
[Laughing]

16
00:01:22,529 --> 00:01:25,659
That’s one example.

17
00:01:25,839 --> 00:01:29,881
But that idea, “I am the Lord 
of all I survey, I am the centre.”

18
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:33,994
The narcissistic centre,
an egocentric conception

19
00:01:33,994 --> 00:01:39,910
of ourselves and the world—
everything is meant to please me.

20
00:01:40,868 --> 00:01:42,458
That which pleases me 
is good,
 

21
00:01:42,458 --> 00:01:46,698
that which does not please me 
is bad.

22
00:01:46,698 --> 00:01:54,773
To reconfigure ourselves 
along the lines of theocentricity—

23
00:01:54,773 --> 00:01:59,989
what is pleasing to Kṛṣṇa,
and by extension, His devotees—

24
00:01:59,989 --> 00:02:04,490
ānukūlyasya saṅkalpaḥ
prātikūlyasya varjanam
[Hbv: 11.417]

25
00:02:04,490 --> 00:02:10,770
A new standard for judging,
what is good and bad;

26
00:02:10,774 --> 00:02:14,162
desirable, undesirable;
progressive, regressive;

27
00:02:14,162 --> 00:02:17,042
evolving, devolving.

28
00:02:17,042 --> 00:02:21,832
New criteria
for making those assessments.

29
00:02:22,221 --> 00:02:30,318
So then, now withdrawing 
from the plane of exploitation,

30
00:02:31,228 --> 00:02:34,207
putting my energy 
towards dedication,

31
00:02:34,207 --> 00:02:38,311
then we are acquiring 
dedicating tendencies.

32
00:02:39,031 --> 00:02:41,891
As we acquire 
dedicating tendencies—
 

33
00:02:41,891 --> 00:02:46,750
the old self is dissolving,
and vanishing,
 

34
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:53,500
and a new self
is manifesting.

35
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:56,510
Once Guru Mahārāj 
compared it to,

36
00:02:56,510 --> 00:03:00,430
he said,
“As you go, say, East

37
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:06,695
you proceed East, automatically 
you are withdrawing from West.

38
00:03:06,695 --> 00:03:09,732
So we are going to think, “Well,
I want to withdraw from West.”

39
00:03:09,732 --> 00:03:12,112
No, just go East.

40
00:03:13,542 --> 00:03:15,432
Go in the Eastern direction,

41
00:03:15,432 --> 00:03:18,392
and automatically 
you’ll withdraw from West.

42
00:03:18,392 --> 00:03:20,537
That’s what it’s like.

43
00:03:20,537 --> 00:03:24,741
And you’ll see yourself 
in a new light, with a new form

44
00:03:24,741 --> 00:03:27,741
that’s constructed
of dedicating tendencies.

45
00:03:27,741 --> 00:03:36,901
All other concepts of self 
are misconceived identities,

46
00:03:36,902 --> 00:03:40,464
false notions of the self.

47
00:03:40,764 --> 00:03:43,153
Guru Mahārāj says, 
“We learn from Einstein
 

48
00:03:43,153 --> 00:03:46,623
that reality is a thing
plus its potential.”

49
00:03:46,623 --> 00:03:54,707
Our potential is as servitors 
in the spiritual domain.

50
00:03:54,707 --> 00:04:00,627
Without that, to the degree
that is absent—

51
00:04:00,627 --> 00:04:02,821
we are in an unreal, 
unrealistic,
 

52
00:04:02,821 --> 00:04:11,341
untenable state of self
or existence.

53
00:04:12,671 --> 00:04:14,827
So reality is a thing
plus its potential.
 

54
00:04:14,827 --> 00:04:17,257
The reality 
of ‘who you are’,

55
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:21,377
so when your serving potential 
is activated.

56
00:04:23,134 --> 00:04:27,814
That’s sevā, seva-mayo yam loka—
the world of sevā.

